About this hotel

Set among shops and restaurants on a pedestrian lane in quaint El Raval, this posh hotel built in 1859 is a 3-minute walk from both Liceu train station and the 19th-century Gran Teatre del Liceu opera house.

Check-in time: 3:00 PM
Check-out time: 11:00 AM

    El Raval

    El Raval is a vibrant area, with cutting-edge exhibitions at the Barcelona Museum of Contemporary Art and adjacent Centre de Cultura Contemporània de Barcelona. Bohemian bars, hip design shops and street art fill the surrounding streets. La Boqueria market on La Rambla avenue sells seafood, wine and tapas, while laid-back cafes line Rambla del Raval. The Maritime Museum displays replica boats in medieval shipyards.

    About this hotel

    Set among shops and restaurants on a pedestrian lane in quaint El Raval, this posh hotel built in 1859 is a 3-minute walk from both Liceu train station and the 19th-century Gran Teatre del Liceu opera house.…

    Sophisticated rooms feature minibars, free Wi-Fi and flat-screen TVs. Upgraded rooms add Nespresso coffee machines, and/or balconies or patios; suites come with whirlpool tubs and living rooms. An airy upgraded suite offers a smart TV, a sofabed and a terrace. Room service is available.

    Amenities include a plush restaurant with high ceilings, and a rooftop terrace with a sleek bar, a pool and a sundeck.
